{"title_page": "Birendra Shah", "text_new": "{{About|the Nepalese journalist|the former King of Nepal|Birendra of Nepal}}\n{{Infobox person\n| honorific_prefix   = \n| name               =  Birendra Shah<!-- include middle initial, if not specified in birth_name -->\n| honorific_suffix   = \n| image              =  Birendra-Shah.jpg\n| image_size         = 150x159\n| alt                = \n| caption            = \n| native_name        = \n| native_name_lang   = \n| pronunciation      = \n| birth_name         =  <!-- only use if different from name above -->\n| birth_date         =  <!-- {{birth date and age|YYYY|MM|DD}} for living people supply only the year unless the exact date is already widely published, as per [[WP:DOB]] -->\n| birth_place        = Inarwasira\n| baptised           =  <!-- will not display if birth_date is entered -->\n| disappeared_date   =  October 4/5, 2007<!-- {{disappeared date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (disappeared date then birth date) -->\n| disappeared_place  = Pipara Bazaar, Kalaiya, Bara, Nepal\n| disappeared_status = Killed\n| death_date         =  <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (death date then birth date) -->\n| death_place        = \n| death_cause        = \n| body_discovered    = November 8, 2007\n| resting_place      = \n| resting_place_coordinates =  <!-- {{coord|LAT|LONG|type:landmark|display=inline}} -->\n| burial_place       =  <!-- may be used instead of resting_place and resting_place_coordinates (displays \"Burial place\" as label) -->\n| burial_coordinates =  <!-- {{coord|LAT|LONG|type:landmark|display=inline}} -->\n| monuments          = \n| residence          = \n| nationality        = Nepalese\n| other_names        = \n| ethnicity          =  <!-- Ethnicity should be supported with a citation from a reliable source -->\n| citizenship        = \n| education          = \n| alma_mater         = \n| occupation         = Journalist\n| years_active       = \n| era                = \n| employer           =  Nepal FM, ''Dristi Weekly'', and Avenues TV\n| organization       = \n| agent              =  <!-- Discouraged in most cases, specifically when promotional, and requiring a reliable source -->\n| known_for          = \n| notable_works      =  <!-- produces label \"Notable work\"; may be overridden by |credits=, which produces label \"Notable credit(s)\"; or by |works=, which produces label \"Works\" -->\n| style              = \n| home_town          = \n| salary             = \n| net_worth          =  <!-- Net worth should be supported with a citation from a reliable source -->\n| height             =  <!-- \"X cm\", \"X m\"  or \"X ft Y in\" plus optional reference (conversions are automatic) -->\n| weight             =  <!-- \"X kg\", \"X lb\" or \"X st Y lb\" plus optional reference (conversions are automatic) -->\n| television         = \n| title              = \n| term               = \n| predecessor        = \n| successor          = \n| party              = \n| movement           = \n| opponents          = \n| boards             = \n| religion           =  <!-- Religion should be supported with a citation from a reliable source -->\n| denomination       =  <!-- Denomination should be supported with a citation from a reliable source -->\n| criminal_charge    =  <!-- Criminality parameters should be supported with citations from reliable sources -->\n| criminal_penalty   = \n| criminal_status    = \n| spouse             = Umarawati Devi\n| children           = Bibek Shah\n| parents            = Deven Shah\n| relatives          = \n| callsign           = \n| awards             = \n| website            =  <!-- {{URL|example.com}} -->\n| module             = \n| module2            = \n| module3            = \n| module4            = \n| module5            = \n| module6            = \n| signature          = \n| signature_size     = \n| signature_alt      = \n| footnotes          = \n}}'''Birendra Shah''' ({{lang-ne|\u092c\u0940\u0930\u0947\u0928\u094d\u0926\u094d\u0930 \u0936\u093e\u0939}}) (Unknown &ndash; November 8, 2007) was a print and broadcast journalist for the Nepal FM, ''Dristi Weekly'', and [[Avenues Television|Avenues TV]]  in [[Bara District|Bara]]. [[Nepal]] was kidnapped October 4/5, 2007, by [[Communist Party of Nepal (Maoist)|Communist Party of Nepal]] [[Maoists]] from Pipara Bazaar, [[Kalaiya]], Bara, Nepal, and found dead one month later.<ref name=protectionline>{{cite web|url=http://protectionline.org/2007/10/09/birendra-shah-journalist-abducted-in-bara-whereabouts-are-still-unknown/|title=Birendra Shah: Journalist abducted in Bara, whereabouts are still unknown  - Protectionline|work=Protectionline}}</ref><ref name=cpj>{{cite web|url=https://cpj.org/killed/2007/birendra-shah.php|title=Birendra Shah|publisher=Committee to Protect Journalists}}</ref><ref name=ucla1>{{cite web|url=http://www.international.ucla.edu/cnes/article/79881|title=NEPAL: Sitaula confirms Maoist involvement in journalist Shah's abduction|publisher=}}</ref> The CPN(M) later issued a statement confirming his death.<ref name=\"bbc1\">{{cite news |title= Nepal Maoist leader apologizes for journalist's murder |work= BBC Worldwide Monitoring |publisher= Lexis-Nexis |date= 2007-11-08 }}</ref>\n\n== Personal ==\nMarried to Umarawati Devi with two children.\n\n== Death ==\n<!--begin wikitable-->{{Location map+|Nepal| width = 250\n | float = left\n |caption= Kalaiya, in the Bara district, is located in Nepal and shown relative to the capital Kathmandu.\n |alt =  Kalaiya is in Nepal\n |AlternativeMap = \n |places=\n  {{Location map~ | Nepal\n  |lat_deg=27 |lat_min=42 |lat_sec=10.3356 |lat_dir=N\n  |lon_deg=85 |lon_min=19 |lon_sec=5.6784 |lon_dir=E \n  |position=left\n  |background=#FFFFFF \n  |label=Kathmandu\n  }}\n  {{Location map~ | Nepal\n  |lat_deg=27 |lat_min=1 |lat_sec=56 |lat_dir=N\n  |lon_deg=85 |lon_min=0 |lon_sec=10 |lon_dir=E \n  |position=right\n  |background=#FFFFFF \n  |label=Kalaiya\n  }}\n }}<!--end wikitable-->Shah was kidnapped after exposing the Maoists and connections to [[illegal logging]] deals. Three members of the Maoists abducted Shah, took him to a forest, and then shot him to death same day he was kidnapped.<ref name=voanews>{{cite web|url=http://www.voanews.com/content/a-13-2007-11-09-voa14-66803612/373958.html|title=Funeral Held for Murdered Nepalese Journalist|work=VOA}}</ref>\n\n== Context ==\nShah exposed illegal logging deals related to the Maoists. Before his death, he had written several reports about the Maoists which resulted in many threats from the party. They abducted and killed him the same day in a forest and threw his body in a swampy forest. Members of Maoist first denied the abduction and killing of the journalist but then after a month admitted to the killing. The abduction and killing was part of a \"personal vendetta\".<ref name=voanews /><ref name=highbeam>{{cite web|url=https://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P3-1378095671.html|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160911183434/https://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P3-1378095671.html|url-status=dead|archive-date=2016-09-11|title=Outcry in Nepal after Maoists admit to killing journalist}}</ref>\n\n== Impact == \nShah has been given a television journalism award in his memory from Avenues Television production.<ref name=ucla4>{{cite web|url=http://web.international.ucla.edu/institute/article/81635|title=NEPAL: Journalist Shah's last rites performed|publisher=}}</ref>\n\n== Reactions ==\nHis death drew criticism from several [[press freedom]] organizations, including [[Reporters Without Borders]],<ref name=\"rwb\">{{cite web | author = Reporters without Borders | title = Maoists confess that journalist Birendra Shah was killed the day he was kidnapped | url = http://www.rsf.org/article.php3?id_article=23915 | accessdate = 2007-11-18 | url-status = dead | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20071030162827/http://www.rsf.org/article.php3?id_article=23915 | archivedate = 2007-10-30 }}</ref> the [[Committee to Protect Journalists]],<ref name=\"cpjarticle\">{{cite web| author = Committee to Protect Journalists | title = Nepal's Birendra Shah is dead, Maoists say | url= http://www.cpj.org/news/2007/asia/nepal05nov07na.html | accessdate = 2007-11-18}}</ref> and the [[International Federation of Journalists]].<ref name=\"asiamed\">{{cite web | title = NEPAL: IFJ outraged at the death of Birendra Shah | url = http://www.asiamedia.ucla.edu/article-southasia.asp?parentid=81528 | accessdate = 2007-11-18 | url-status = dead | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20110520085211/http://www.asiamedia.ucla.edu/article-southasia.asp?parentid=81528 | archivedate = 2011-05-20 }}</ref> There were multiple calls for justice and a nationwide protest.<ref name=voanews /><ref name=highbeam /><ref name=ucla4 />\n\nMore than a month after the killing, Maoist Deputy Commander Janardan Sharma Prabhakar apologized on behalf of his party, which had previously claimed innocence.<ref name=\"bbc2\">{{cite news|title= Abducted Nepal journalist's body found| work= \"BBC Worldwide Monitoring | publisher = Lexis-Nexis | date= 2007-11-08 }}</ref>  <!-- The killing was also comdemned by [[Binaya Dhoj Chanda]], of the [[Nepali Congress]].<ref name=\"bbc1\"/> comment; the killing was condemned by all sectors of the nepali political scene, not just NC-->\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Shah, Birendra}}\n[[Category:Murdered journalists]]\n[[Category:Nepalese journalists]]\n[[Category:Nepalese murder victims]]\n[[Category:Kidnapped Nepalese people]]\n[[Category:People murdered in Nepal]]\n[[Category:2007 deaths]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing]]\n[[Category:Kidnappings in Nepal]]\n\n\n{{nepal-journalist-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{About|the Nepalese journalist|the former King of Nepal|Birendra of Nepal}}\n{{Infobox person\n| honorific_prefix   = \n| name               =  Birendra Shah<!-- include middle initial, if not specified in birth_name -->\n| honorific_suffix   = \n| image              =